sentences: Born in Newcastle, New South Wales in 1887.
He contributed songs to pantomime The Bunyip (1916).
On 17th August 1951 he collapsed in a Dubbo hotel lobby and died suddenly.
Corroboree Rag (1916) in The Bunyip Pantomime
That little home among the hills (1920)
He was prominent in the early twentieth century.
For several years he was a key member of impersonator revue Stiffy and Mo, with fellow vaudeville personality Roy Rene.
